{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel-B shell forwarder that plugs between the shell and the kernel: it takes a tool request, applies a deny-default verb-level capability check, and only if the verb is on the allow-set submits the request to the kernel through the portal (mmapping the inherited region memfd fd5, then transmit-request-through-portal-region-awaiting-reply); a denied verb is rejected without running. The reply (or the denial) is written to the out_path from the request. As a kernel descendant it inherits the portal fds; reuses the test-submitter mapping pattern and the portal submit primitive. The allow-set is small for now (read-only verbs) and is intended to be replaced by a smarter policy later; it is a whitelist (deny-default), never a blacklist.","module_name":"forward-capability-checked-request-toward-kernel-portal","package_name":"forward-capability-checked-request-toward-kernel-portal","function_definitions":{"forward-capability-checked-request-toward-kernel-portal":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"prot","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"mapshared","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c16384","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16384},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_out","variable_type":"str","assignment_o